              <p align="left"><a href="http://business.newsforge.com/business/05/08/03/1258246.shtml?tid=138&tid=3"><strong> <span class="style2">Mozilla Foundation forms for-profit corporation</span></strong></a><span class="style2"><br>
                  <strong>NewsForge, Mountain View, CA, August 3, 2005</strong>&nbsp;-- The Mozilla Foundation, a non-profit public benefit software development organization, today announced it has formed a wholly owned subsidiary company to be known as the Mozilla Corporation. The Mozilla Corporation is a taxable subsidiary that serves the non-profit, public benefit goals of its parent, the Mozilla Foundation, and the vast Mozilla community. It will continue to leverage resources from diverse sources to create and distribute great open and free-of-charge end-user products -- such as the popular Mozilla Firefox Web browser and Mozilla Thunderbird email client -- that promote choice and innovation on the Web. <a href="http://business.newsforge.com/business/05/08/03/1258246.shtml?tid=138&tid=3"> ...Full Story</a></span></p>
